                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I love this idea...especially the part about the horsemanship skill, which would increase your agility while on a horse (faster stops and starts, and greater control turning).  I think your skill with a horse should improve with training.  That idea is consistent with how things are normally done in EQ, and frankly, I'm surprized that this (or something like it) wasn't in the original design.<br /><br />I totally agree that being on a horse and all of the BS that goes along with it should have great benefits, beyond speed and constant meditation.  It makes sense that certain defensive and offensive advantages should be given to those on horseback, both from a RP standpoint and logically; and those advantages should increase based on your lvl of skill and/or the quality (cost) of your mount.<br /><br />I've said it before, I'll say it again; there is more creativity in the average player of this game than is in the entire SOE corporation.  They would do well to listen to some of these ideas ocassionally.<br /><br />/rant off</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
